class Solution {
    public long maximumOr(int[] nums, int k) {
        long res = 0, mask = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            mask |= num;
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            res = Math.max(res, (long) (nums[i] << k) | (mask & ~nums[i]));
        }
        return res;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the array once to find the bitwise OR of all numbers and then iterates through the array again to find the maximum possible value by shifting each number to the left by k places and combining it with the bitwise OR of the remaining numbers.
